Description:
Gametogenesis, fertilization, embryogenesis, organogenesis, normal/abnormal embryological development;
emphasizing mammal; amphibian, bird illustrating general principles and concepts. Laboratory studies of frog,
chick, pig developmental anatomy. Three one hour lectures and one three hour lab.

(Cross-listed with BSCI 50363 and BSCI 70363) Microbial interactions with their biotic and abiotic
environment; control of distribution and physiological activities; biochemical cycles; current techniques;
emphasis on bacteria in aquatic systems.
